cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper presents a software system based on computational learning algorithms to optimize waste collection routes and predict container fill levels. This involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.DS. The system also involves data analysis and prediction, which can be categorized under cs.SI. Finally, the system has practical applications in urban waste management, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE.
